# Session handoffs

## Active handoffs

- [2026-06-20-32bit-and-zonein-optimizations.md](2026-06-20-32bit-and-zonein-optimizations.md) â€” 
**DONE + pushed 2026-06-20.** The "32-bit memory leak" task: the leak was already fixed (bytecode 
cache, re-measured flat); fixed three *other* issues â€” `D3DCREATE_FPU_PRESERVE` (32-bit cantina 
see-through), `/LARGEADDRESSAWARE` (32-bit Debug runnable), and a zone-in load-smoothness set: #1 
disk VS shader cache, #4 elapsedTime clamp (`minFrameRate`), #2 interior-layout throttle 
(`maxInteriorCreatesPerFrame`, safe count-on-CellProperty). 5 commits 
`db040db29`/`b4749ea9a`/`16f4e58ec`/`272906c2b`/`b4860e0bc`. **OPEN follow-ups:** back-room 
chase-cam clip (pre-existing, door-snap pull-in), `_ITERATOR_DEBUG_LEVEL=2â†’1` (global ABI, 
deferred), texture pre-warm. Memory: `project_zonein_load_jerk_optimizations` + the two 32-bit 
memories. Consults: CONSULT-45/46.

- [2026-06-20-32bit-cantina-leak-NEXT.md](2026-06-20-32bit-cantina-leak-NEXT.md) â€” **RESOLVED 
2026-06-20.** The original "leak-induced camera fling" diagnosis was WRONG. It was TWO things: (1) 
the "see Mos Eisley from inside the cantina" (screenshots 0386-0389) = a **D3D9-on-32-bit FP bug** 
â€” `Direct3d9::CreateDevice` missing `D3DCREATE_FPU_PRESERVE` clamped the x87 FPU to single 
precision â†’ degraded the shared portal-visibility math â†’ deterministic see-through-wall at one 
spot; **FIXED** (one line, gl05/06/07 Win32 rebuilt, gl05 runtime-verified); and (2) the **actual 2 
GB leak is already fixed** by the Phase-32 VS bytecode cache (`ff02a367e`) â€” re-measured flat 
(~900 MB plateau). Localized by a rendererÃ—bitness matrix at the exact spot (gl05-32bit only). 
Memory: `project_d3d9_32bit_fpu_preserve_cantina_seethrough`. Carry-forward: rebuild x64 gl05/06/07 
for source consistency; commit pending.
- [2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-FIX-COMPLETE.md](2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-FIX-COMPLETE.md) â€” 
**DONE 2026-06-20, committed `3549c7104`.** The cantina door-snap was **TWO stacked bugs**: (1) 
avatar floor-collision rubberband â€” footprint **circle** grazes an uncrossable floor-mesh seam 
while the **center** walks clean (`PWR_WalkOk`); fixed by suppressing that contact only on a 
**shallow graze** (`cs_seamGrazeEpsilon`); and (2) chase-camera instant snaps (zoom pull-in + 
shoulder zero), fixed by **rate-limiting the inward ease** (`cs_cameraPullInSpeed`). The resolver 
slide was never broken; framerate was a real factor for bug 1 only. Root-caused by runtime probes, 
**4-AI code-reviewed**, built clean in all 4 configs (Win32/x64 Ã— Debug/Release), user-verified. 
All `CORNERSNAP-*` probes removed. Remaining: commit + a systemic non-dt-scaled-constant sweep 
(backlog). Tunables ref: `spikes/door-snap-fix-tunables.md`.
- [2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-spike-START.md](2026-06-20-cantina-door-snap-spike-START.md) â€” 
_historical START handoff (root-cause findings before the fix); superseded by FIX-COMPLETE above._

- [login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md](login-music-miles-9.3v-research.md) â€” **RESOLVED 2026-06-18 
(`5a894d327`).** Login/character-select SCREEN music now plays. The 9.3v lead was a **red herring** 
â€” the bug was engine-side, not a Miles version difference: Miles' background IO thread re-opens 
the stream via our `AIL_set_file_callbacks` hook with an **empty filename** â†’ `TreeFile::open("")` 
returned NULL â†’ buffers never filled. Fix (`clientAudio/Audio.cpp`, gated 
`s_titleMusicStreamFix`): remember the real stream name + serve the empty-name re-open from it + 
track/seek read offset across re-opens + close prior handles (leak guard). Verified: plays 
start-to-finish, transitions to zone music, handles bounded. (9.3v was later adopted for x64 in 
`984afc073` for a **separate** in-game 3D-audio mixer bug.) Handoff kept as historical record.
- [phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md](phase-32-d3dcompile-port.md) â€” **Phase 32 (D3DX â†’ 
d3dcompiler_47).** 32-01 GATE = PASS + 32-02 (D3DCompile / HlslRewrite / X4016 fix / VS bytecode 
cache) COMPLETE & committed; renders correctly (user-verified). Hit a **32-bit Debug-client memory 
issue** â€” D3DCompile's per-compile heap fragmentation bloats first cantina load past the 2 GB 
ceiling (~59s); the bytecode cache fixes re-entry recompiles but not first-load misses. **Moving 
forward anyway: deferred to x64 (NOT reverted) â€” the x64 port removes the 2 GB ceiling and 
dissolves the OOM.** Next session = v3.0 x64 milestone (Phase 33 `x64-build-platform`). 2026-06-17.

