codex
**1. Coverage**

`Graphics::resize(int,int)` callers:

- [Graphics.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.c
pp:1015): deferred gl11 path in `Graphics::beginScene()`. Runs only when `ms_resizePending && 
ms_firstPresentDone` [Graphics.cpp:1004](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraph
ics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004), so post-first-present.
- [CutScene.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/CutScene
.cpp:209): `CutScene::start()` forces `640x480` for small non-stretch videos. This bypasses the new 
gl11 `displayModeChanged` deferral and can run synchronously if a cutscene starts before first real 
present.
- [CutScene.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/CutScene
.cpp:264): `CutScene::stop()` restores saved dimensions. Also bypasses the deferral, but normally 
post-start and likely post-present unless a cutscene is started/stopped during startup.

gl11 `displayModeChanged` hook invocation sites:

- Hook is installed at [Graphics.cpp:313](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGrap
hics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:313).
- `WM_EXITSIZEMOVE` flushes pending size change at [Os.cpp:1177](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/sh
ared/library/sharedFoundation/src/win32/Os.cpp:1177).
- `WM_SIZE` calls it outside interactive sizing at [Os.cpp:1292](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/sh
ared/library/sharedFoundation/src/win32/Os.cpp:1292).
- `WM_DISPLAYCHANGE` calls it at [Os.cpp:1298](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/share
dFoundation/src/win32/Os.cpp:1298).

For gl11, `GraphicsNamespace::displayModeChanged()` now records width/height and returns at [Graphics
.cpp:403-438](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:
403), so those hook paths do not synchronously reach `Graphics::resize` or `ms_api->resize`.

Bypass hole: `CutScene::start()` and `CutScene::stop()` still synchronously reach `Graphics::resize` 
[CutScene.cpp:209](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/CutSce
ne.cpp:209), [CutScene.cpp:264](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/share
d/core/CutScene.cpp:264). The D3D11 plugin guards only `!Direct3d11_Device::isInstalled()` [Direct3d1
1.cpp:211](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:2
11); once installed, those cutscene calls still run the device-lost callbacks, `resizeBackBuffer`, 
and restored callbacks [Direct3d11.cpp:214-219](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/
Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:214). That is the one real synchronous startup bypass I see.

**2. Liveness / Lost Resize**

Main client loop order is stable: `Os::update()` first [Game.cpp:1072](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/eng
ine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1072), draw block only if `!isOver()` [Game.cp
p:1197-1199](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:119
7), then `Graphics::update()` [Game.cpp:1204](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/client
Game/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1204), `Graphics::beginScene()` [Game.cpp:1205](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/
src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1205), `Graphics::endScene()` [Game.cpp
:1218](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1218), 
then `Graphics::present()` [Game.cpp:1225](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGam
e/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1225).

So after the first real `Graphics::present()` flips `ms_firstPresentDone` [Graphics.cpp:1119](/D:/Cod
e/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1119), the next 
non-terminal frame calls `Graphics::beginScene()` and applies the pending resize [Graphics.cpp:1004-1
015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004).

It can defer forever only if the game never reaches a real present: `Os::update()` returns false and 
exits before draw [Game.cpp:1125-1129](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/sr
c/shared/core/Game.cpp:1125), or `isOver()` becomes true before draw [Game.cpp:1197-1199](/D:/Code/sw
g-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1197). In that case there 
is no later frame to resize for.

**3. Reentrancy / Safe Point**

The resize is applied before `Graphics` marks begin open and before plugin `beginScene`: deferred 
resize happens at [Graphics.cpp:1004-1015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGra
phics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004), `_DEBUG` `ms_haveBegin = true` is after that [Graphics.cpp:1019-1
020](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1019), 
then `ms_api->beginScene()` runs [Graphics.cpp:1023-1024](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/li
brary/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1023). That is a good no-half-open-scene point.

D3D11 `resizeBackBuffer()` releases RTV/DSV refs and calls `ClearState()` before `ResizeBuffers` [Dir
ect3d11_Device.cpp:1217-1223](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win
32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:1217), then `Direct3d11_Device::beginScene()` rebinds back-buffer RTV/DSV [D
irect3d11_Device.cpp:923-924](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win
32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:923). That avoids the common ResizeBuffers “RT still bound” conflict.

Reentrancy looks okay: `ms_resizePending` is cleared before `Graphics::resize()` [Graphics.cpp:1006](
/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1006). If a 
nested `WM_SIZE` occurs during resize, gl11 `displayModeChanged()` only records a new pending size 
and returns [Graphics.cpp:425-438](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/sr
c/win32/Graphics.cpp:425), so no recursive resize.

**4. First-Present Gate**

Install-time D3D11 clear/present does not go through `Graphics::present()`. 
`Direct3d11_Device::create()` calls `Direct3d11_Device::beginScene()`, `clearViewport()`, 
`endScene()`, and `Direct3d11_Device::present()` directly [Direct3d11_Device.cpp:628-631](/D:/Code/sw
g-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:628). The gate 
flips only in `Graphics::present()` [Graphics.cpp:1115-1119](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client
/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1115) or `Graphics::present(HWND,...)` [Graphics.cpp:1
125-1131](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1125
). So the install-time present does not mark first present done.

**5. Defers Forever Cases**

For the normal SWG client loop, no: once any real frame presents, the next frame begins and applies 
the latest pending size [Game.cpp:1205](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/s
rc/shared/core/Game.cpp:1205), [Graphics.cpp:1004-1015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/libr
ary/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004).

Possible forever cases:

- The client never reaches `Graphics::present()` because it exits/aborts before draw [Game.cpp:1125-1
129](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1125), [Gam
e.cpp:1197-1199](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp
:1197).
- Non-client/editor paths using `Graphics::present(HWND,...)` with gl11 are suspect because D3D11 
`presentToWindow` is still stubbed [Direct3d11.cpp:1093-1104](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/clien
t/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:1093), while `Game::runGameLoopOnce(true,...)` 
uses that path [Game.cpp:1222-1223](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/s
hared/core/Game.cpp:1222). Not the standalone SWG client path, but it would prevent the gate from 
flipping successfully in those hosts.
- Minor lifecycle hole: `ms_firstPresentDone` and pending flags are static-initialized only [Graphics
.cpp:94-97](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:94
); I found no reset on install/remove [Graphics.cpp:176](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/lib
rary/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:176), [Graphics.cpp:351-366](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/en
gine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:351). If graphics can be 
removed/reinstalled in-process, the first-present gate would stay true from the prior install.
