- `WM_DISPLAYCHANGE` calls it at [Os.cpp:1298](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/shared/library/sharedFoundation/src/win32/Os.cpp:1298).

For gl11, `GraphicsNamespace::displayModeChanged()` now records width/height and returns at [Graphics.cpp:403-438](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:403), so those hook paths do not synchronously reach `Graphics::resize` or `ms_api->resize`.

Bypass hole: `CutScene::start()` and `CutScene::stop()` still synchronously reach `Graphics::resize` [CutScene.cpp:209](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/CutScene.cpp:209), [CutScene.cpp:264](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/CutScene.cpp:264). The D3D11 plugin guards only `!Direct3d11_Device::isInstalled()` [Direct3d11.cpp:211](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:211); once installed, those cutscene calls still run the device-lost callbacks, `resizeBackBuffer`, and restored callbacks [Direct3d11.cpp:214-219](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:214). That is the one real synchronous startup bypass I see.

**2. Liveness / Lost Resize**

Main client loop order is stable: `Os::update()` first [Game.cpp:1072](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1072), draw block only if `!isOver()` [Game.cpp:1197-1199](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1197), then `Graphics::update()` [Game.cpp:1204](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1204), `Graphics::beginScene()` [Game.cpp:1205](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1205), `Graphics::endScene()` [Game.cpp:1218](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1218), then `Graphics::present()` [Game.cpp:1225](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1225).

So after the first real `Graphics::present()` flips `ms_firstPresentDone` [Graphics.cpp:1119](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1119), the next non-terminal frame calls `Graphics::beginScene()` and applies the pending resize [Graphics.cpp:1004-1015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004).

It can defer forever only if the game never reaches a real present: `Os::update()` returns false and exits before draw [Game.cpp:1125-1129](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1125), or `isOver()` becomes true before draw [Game.cpp:1197-1199](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1197). In that case there is no later frame to resize for.

**3. Reentrancy / Safe Point**

The resize is applied before `Graphics` marks begin open and before plugin `beginScene`: deferred resize happens at [Graphics.cpp:1004-1015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004), `_DEBUG` `ms_haveBegin = true` is after that [Graphics.cpp:1019-1020](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1019), then `ms_api->beginScene()` runs [Graphics.cpp:1023-1024](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1023). That is a good no-half-open-scene point.

D3D11 `resizeBackBuffer()` releases RTV/DSV refs and calls `ClearState()` before `ResizeBuffers` [Direct3d11_Device.cpp:1217-1223](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:1217), then `Direct3d11_Device::beginScene()` rebinds back-buffer RTV/DSV [Direct3d11_Device.cpp:923-924](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:923). That avoids the common ResizeBuffers “RT still bound” conflict.

Reentrancy looks okay: `ms_resizePending` is cleared before `Graphics::resize()` [Graphics.cpp:1006](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1006). If a nested `WM_SIZE` occurs during resize, gl11 `displayModeChanged()` only records a new pending size and returns [Graphics.cpp:425-438](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:425), so no recursive resize.

**4. First-Present Gate**

Install-time D3D11 clear/present does not go through `Graphics::present()`. `Direct3d11_Device::create()` calls `Direct3d11_Device::beginScene()`, `clearViewport()`, `endScene()`, and `Direct3d11_Device::present()` directly [Direct3d11_Device.cpp:628-631](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11_Device.cpp:628). The gate flips only in `Graphics::present()` [Graphics.cpp:1115-1119](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1115) or `Graphics::present(HWND,...)` [Graphics.cpp:1125-1131](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1125). So the install-time present does not mark first present done.

**5. Defers Forever Cases**

For the normal SWG client loop, no: once any real frame presents, the next frame begins and applies the latest pending size [Game.cpp:1205](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1205), [Graphics.cpp:1004-1015](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:1004).

Possible forever cases:

- The client never reaches `Graphics::present()` because it exits/aborts before draw [Game.cpp:1125-1129](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1125), [Game.cpp:1197-1199](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1197).
- Non-client/editor paths using `Graphics::present(HWND,...)` with gl11 are suspect because D3D11 `presentToWindow` is still stubbed [Direct3d11.cpp:1093-1104](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/application/Direct3d11/src/win32/Direct3d11.cpp:1093), while `Game::runGameLoopOnce(true,...)` uses that path [Game.cpp:1222-1223](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/Game.cpp:1222). Not the standalone SWG client path, but it would prevent the gate from flipping successfully in those hosts.
- Minor lifecycle hole: `ms_firstPresentDone` and pending flags are static-initialized only [Graphics.cpp:94-97](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:94); I found no reset on install/remove [Graphics.cpp:176](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:176), [Graphics.cpp:351-366](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGraphics/src/win32/Graphics.cpp:351). If graphics can be removed/reinstalled in-process, the first-present gate would stay true from the prior install.
